<% provide(:title, 'Add Users') %>
<h1>Add Users</h1>
<h2>Instructions</h2>
<p>Please enter a list of <%= User.cas_auth? ? 'CAS usernames' : 'e-mail addresses' %>, either separated by commas or one per line (you can copy and paste a list out of Excel, for example). The system will attempt to look them up in the directory service and create user accounts for them if they are found.</p>
<%= simple_form_for @enrollment do |f| %>
  <%= f.input :ids, as: :text %>
  <%= f.input :role, collection: @roles, selected: 'student', label_method: :humanize %>
  <%= f.submit 'Submit' %>
<% end %>
<%= link_to 'Cancel', users_path %>
